<HEAD>Heart-Liver Transplant Patient Discharged</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 11-year-old girl who was the world's first
recipient of a heart-liver transplant was released from the hospital
following surgery to clear blocked bile ducts.
   Stormie Jones of White Settlement, Texas, was released Monday
from Children's Hospital of Pittsburgh in fair condition and was
scheduled to return home immediately, said a hospital spokeswoman.
   She was admitted to the hospital Oct. 26 because doctors feared
she was rejecting her organs. But she began improving after doctors
performed surgery Nov. 8 to clear the blockages.
   Stormie received her transplants on Valentine's Day 1984. She
needed the transplant because of a rare congenital disease that
increased the cholesterol in her blood to dangerous levels.
   She is the only surviving recipient of the double transplant.
</TEXT>
