<HEAD>15-Month-Old Child Found Dead Ten Days After Abduction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ESLOHE, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The kidnapped 15-month-old son of a
West German millionaire was found dead today, ten days after he was
seized during a bloody break-in at his parents' house, police said.
   The boy's 56-year-old grandmother was strangled in the Nov. 12
attempted robbery at the home of Christian Padberg, a wealthy
building material trader.
   The intruder then fled with 15-month-old Patrick Padberg and
later demanded several million marks (dollars) in ransom.
   The boy's body was found early this morning not far from his
parents' house, said Juergen Siegert, head of the police team
investigating the crime.
   Police also said a suspect has been arrested in the case, but did
not identify him.
   According to police reports on the Nov. 12 break-in, the intruder
was trying to break open a safe when he was apparently surprised by
the boy's grandmother and great-grandmother.
   The grandmother was strangled, apparently after struggling with
the intruder, who police said locked the baby's 76-year-old
great-grandmother in a room before fleeing with the child.
   The boy's parents were on a vacation in Greece at the time of the
kidnapping.
   Eslohe is about 60 miles northeast of Cologne.
