<HEAD>Wet Winter Storm Chills Northwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A wet winter storm swept through much of the Northwest today,
dumping rain and snow, as gale winds whipped through parts of New
England and snow dusted higher elevations in New Hampshire.
   In the Northwest, the Washington Cascade mountains and the
northwest California mountains had a winter storm watch posted
through tonight, warning of heavy snow and strong winds.
   A similar advisory was in effect through Wednesday for the
Siskiyous mountains of Oregon and the mountains of Idaho.
   Showers extended over northern California, Oregon, northern
Nevada and western Montana early today. It rained in the lower
elevations and snowed in the mountains.
   In New England, gale winds swept through coastal areas. Three
inches of snow fell on Mount Washington in northern New Hampshire
this morning.
   Elsewhere, rain extended from west central Florida through the
northeast part of the state.
   Tropical storm Keith was in the Gulf of Mexico and headed toward
Florida. The storm was moving north-northeast at slightly less than
10 mph. But Keith was expected to take a more easterly path.
   Today's forecast called for scattered rain over central Florida;
rain from the northern and central Pacific Coast to western Idaho,
the Idaho Panhandle and northwest Montana, with snow in higher
elevations, and strong, gusty winds from the northern two-thirds of
the Pacific Coast to the Pacific Northwest and the northern half of
the Rockies.
   High temperatures were forecast in the 20s and 30s in northern
New England and northeast New York, northern and upper Michigan,
Wisconsin, Minnesota and North Dakota; the 40s and 50s from central
New England to North Carolina, the Great Lakes, the Ohio Valley and
the Tennessee Valley, from Iowa and South Dakota to northern
Louisiana and northern Texas, from Montana to central sections of
New Mexico and Arizona, and the northern Pacific states; the 80s in
central and southern Florida, and scattered along the southern coast
of California; and in the 60s and 70s in the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 9
degrees at Williston, N.D., to 80 degrees at Key West and Homestead,
Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 47 partly cloudy; Boston 36 fair; Buffalo 35
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 50 cloudy; Cincinnati Not lable; Cleveland
37 cloudy; Detroit 36 cloudy; Miami 79 partly cloudy; New York 38
fair; Philadelphia 35 fair; Pittsburgh 37 cloudy; Portland, Maine 35
fair; Washington 41 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 18 fair; Chicago 31 cloudy; Dallas-Fort Worth
39 fair; Denver 33 fair; Des Moines 28 fair; Indianapolis 30 fair;
Kansas City 29 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 24 foggy; Nashville 35
fair; New Orleans 53 cloudy; St. Louis 25 foggy.
   _West: Albuquerque 34 fair; Anchorage 20 snow; Las Vegas 43 fair;
Los Angeles 53 fair; Phoenix 52 fair; Salt Lake City 41 cloudy; San
Diego 53 partly cloudy; San Francisco 56 rain; Seattle 44 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 25 fair; Toronto 32 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
