<HEAD>Results From Canadian Parliamentary Election</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Canada-Election, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are official figures from Canada's parliamentary election
Monday, with 95 percent of the returns tabulated. The House of
Commons has a total of 295 seats.
   Progressive Conservative Party, headed by Prime Minister Brian
Mulroney: 169 seats, down from 211.
   Liberal Party, led by John Turner: 82 seats, up from 40.
   New Democratic Party, headed by Ed Broadbent: 44 seats, up from
30.
   The popular vote broke down to about 43 percent for the
Conservatives, 32 percent for the Liberals and 20 percent for the
New Democrats. About 75 percent of Canada's 17.5 million eligible
voters cast ballots.
