<2ND_LINE>PM-Teen Shot,0279</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Teen Commits Suicide After Best Friend Dies In Accidental Shooting</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Baahlmann is cq in 5th graf</NOTE>
<DATELINE>COLLINSVILLE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 13-year-old boy shot himself in the
head after accidentally killing his best friend while the two played
with a handgun, authorities said.
   The body of James ``J.P.'' Herndon was found Monday in a wooded
ravine near his home, a pistol nearby, two days after his friend
Jacob Viviano, also 13, was accidentally shot to death at James'
home.
   Police believe James had shot himself shortly after his friend
died while the two were playing alone. Because of powder burns and
other physical evidence, police believe that James accidentally shot
Jacob.
   Investigators do not believe any foul play was involved or that a
third person participated, said Lt. Dennis Fischer, chief of
detectives for the county sheriff's department.
   The manner of death in both instances was the same: a single
gunshot wound to the head, said Ralph Baahlmann Jr., chief deputy
coroner for Madison County.
   ``I don't know what they would have been doing with a gun,'' said
August C. Viviano Jr., Jacob's father. ``I just can't believe what
happened. He was such a happy boy.''
   After James' body was found Monday, word spread quickly at
Collinsville North Junior High School, where both boys were
enrolled. Some students wiped away tears as they walked to their
buses.
   Friends and relatives of the boys said they were the best of
friends. They stayed overnight at each other's homes, went together
to the Tepee, a gathering place for teens in Collinsville, and were
widely known as pranksters in the neighborhood.
</TEXT>
