<TEXT>
   White d by
Eleazu S. Obinna, a Pan-African studies professor who has been fired
for his alleged involvement in the grade-selling scheme.
   The appeals hearing was expected to continue through Wednesday on
the suburban San Fernando Valley campus.
   Obinna, a tenured faculty member who had taught at the university
for 17 years, and Willie J. Bellamy, a first-year instructor, told
students the only work required for an A grade in the course,
``Field Work in the African-American Community,'' was to sell 20 $5
