<HEAD>Floods Kill 12 People, Force Thousands to Leave Homes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two days of torrential rains have
caused floods in eight states, killing 12 and forcing 43,000 people
to flee their homes.
   Rain continued to fall in many areas and authorities issued
warnings to residents of low-lying areas near rivers.
   About 25,720 people were evacuated from Kelantan, the worst-hit
state, where many roads were closed and covered with up to 3 feet of
water.
   Schools were shut throughout the flooded areas, including the far
northern state of Perlis, the southern state of Johore, and the
southern states of Negri Sembilan, Malacca and Pahang.
