<HEAD>United Arab Emirates to Buy French Missiles</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ABU DHABI, United Arab Emirates (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The United Arab Emirates
has signed a military pact with France to purchase Crotale
surface-to-air missiles, an army officer said Monday.
   Sheik Khalifa Bin Zayed, deputy supreme commander of the armed
forces, announced the agreement Tuesday at a meeting of senior army
officers, the official news agency WAM reported.
