<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Collapsed Ditch,0158</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Believed Dead After Ditch Collapses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KNOXVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A ditch collapsed Tuesday, burying two
construction workers seven feet underground, authorities said. The
two were presumed dead.
   The unidentified men were digging a sewer line for a housing
subdivision when one side of the trench caved in, said Tammy Brogan
of the Rural-Metro Ambulance Service.
   ``We can confirm there are two victims (buried) six or seven feet
down,'' John Yu, of the Knox County Rescue Squad, said two hours
after the accident. ``We have victims partially exposed at this
time.''
   The victims were working for Blount Excavating, officials said. A
woman who answered the telephone at the Maryville, Tenn., company
said there was no one available to discuss the accident.
   Rescue crews used a backhoe to level out a hill next to the
accident site to keep any more dirt from collapsing. The cause of
the accident was not known.
</TEXT>
