after founder Jim Bakker left amid a sex-and-money scandal.
   Johnson said Heritage Ministries' board of directors will make
its offer during an auction in U.S. Bankruptcy Court in Columbia on
Dec. 12.
   Bankruptcy Judge Rufus Reynolds last week rejected offers as high
as $115 million from Canadians Peter Thomas of Vancouver and Stephen
Mernick of Toronto. He ordered bidding to ``start from scratch'' and
set the Dec. 12 date.
   The judge said if the ministry's assets aren't sold then, he'll
liquidate PTL.
