<HEAD>Announces Plans For 45,000-Square-Foot Attraction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Coca-Cola Co. announced plans Tuesday for
``The World Of Coca-Cola,'' a four-story attraction presenting the
history of the 100-year-old soft drink giant.
   The 45,000-square-foot attraction will be constructed in downtown
Atlanta, adjacent to the Underground Atlanta retail and
entertainment complex. The Coke attraction will open in mid-1990.
   ``In `The World Of Coca-Cola,' innovation and entertainment will
be mingled with memorabilia and nostalgia for each visitor,''
Coca-Cola Chief Executive Officer Roberto C. Goizueta said.
   Plans include ``the most innovative neon outdoor sign ever
created for Coca-Cola.'' A giant neon Coke sign at Margaret Mitchell
Square, which had become an Atlanta landmark, was demolished several
years ago.
